---
import Layout from "@halleyfante/documentation/Layout";
---

<Layout
  title="Extension"
  description="VS Code extension for Pix"
  current="extension"
>
  <p>
    The Pix extension for VS Code provides syntax highlighting and
    autocomplete for <code>.pix</code> files. The language server is
    bundled with the extension.
  </p>

  <h2>Installation</h2>
  <p>
    Download the <code>.vsix</code> file from the
    <a href="https://github.com/halleyfante/pix/releases">releases page</a>
    and install it:
  </p>
  <pre><code>code --install-extension pix-0.1.0.vsix</code></pre>

  <h3>Building from source</h3>
  <pre><code>cd tools/extension
npm ci
npm run package
code --install-extension pix-0.1.0.vsix</code></pre>

  <h2>Features</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Syntax highlighting via TextMate grammar</li>
    <li>Context-aware autocomplete powered by the language server</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Configuration</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Setting</th><th>Description</th><th>Default</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>pix.languageServerPath</code></td>
        <td>Path to the language server binary</td>
        <td>Bundled binary</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</Layout>
